partintro.section:
&reftitle.intro;



 This attribute is used to mark a parameter that is sensitive and should
 have its value redacted if present in a stack trace.

   &reftitle.examples;



<?php
function defaultBehavior(string $secret) {
    debug_print_backtrace();
}

function sensitiveParameterTest(
    #[\SensitiveParameter] string $secret
) {
    throw new Exception('Error!');
}

defaultBehavior('password');
sensitiveParameterTest('password');
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


#0 /in/g7BEP(12): defaultBehavior('password')

Fatal error: Uncaught Exception: Error! in /in/g7BEP:9
Stack trace:
#0 /in/g7BEP(13): sensitiveParameterTest(Object(SensitiveParameterValue))
#1 {main}
  thrown in /in/g7BEP on line 9
